    66	| Classification | ADAPT (heavy) + ACCOMMODATE for validation rules | ALIGN |
    67	
    68	**What it means.** KBM's "everything required" stance reflects their current pain (optional usage = ignored usage). Pivot's "selective enforcement" stance reflects their current state — experienced reps already document well, and forcing the same rigidity on them would be received as a downgrade. The merged company has both populations.
    69	
    70	**Recommendation.** Adopt Pivot's role-based enforcement model. Define performance-tier roles (e.g., "New Rep" — first 6 months; "Underperformer" — flagged via manager review). All reps in those roles get required-field validation. Experienced reps in good standing keep flexibility. KBM's ex-staff inherit the New Rep tier during onboarding and graduate as they demonstrate data discipline.
