   198	
   199	- **REQ-002**: Make opportunity entry required (currently optional) to ensure pipeline visibility and data quality (ADAPT)
   200	  - CRM usage mandatory for all sales/BD activity
   201	  - "Not required - many don't" becomes "Required for accountability"
   202	  - Eliminates "some people just lick everything and calling it theirs"
   203	
   204	- **REQ-003**: Implement validation rules and required fields on opportunities to prevent incomplete data entry (ACCOMMODATE)
   205	  - Minimum fields required: opportunity name, account, contact, value, probability, stage, expected close date, source, territory, owner
   206	  - Validation rules prevent advancing without required information
   207	  - Enforce data quality discipline
   208	
   209	- **REQ-004**: Use Kanban Boards for visual opportunity pipeline management (ALIGNS)
   210	  - Visual drag-and-drop interface for pipeline management
   211	  - See opportunities by stage at a glance
   212	  - "I think it'd be a good tool for us to try and test out" - Matt
   213	
   214	- **REQ-005**: Restrict opportunity visibility to assigned users only (ADAPT)
   215	  - Users see only their own opportunities (not entire company feed)
   216	  - Prevents "doom-scrolling" distraction
   217	  - Focuses activity on owned opportunities
   218	
   219	### 3.2 Current State Process
   220	
   221	**PROCESS**: Opportunity Management (Current State - Data Quality Issues)  
   222	**TRIGGER**: Lead qualified or relationship identified  
   223	**STEPS**:
   224	1. Opportunity may or may not be entered in Zendesk (optional)
   225	2. If entered → minimal information captured (no validation)
   226	3. Some users diligent (document activities, updates); some minimal or none
   227	4. Value estimated (quality varies widely by user)
   228	5. Probability assigned subjectively (no standard by stage)
   229	6. Forecasting unreliable because data quality poor
   230	7. "Poo in, poo out" - Team describing data quality issue
   231	
   232	**PAIN POINTS**: 
   233	- Optional = ignored by many
   234	- No validation = incomplete records
   235	- No standards = inconsistent probabilities
