8","endTime":"09:10","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Chris, maybe you can just mention the chat if you already got that or not.","startTime":"09:12","endTime":"09:16","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm not sure if I should be asking for that on your behalf, but.","startTime":"09:16","endTime":"09:19","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Just let us know if they.","startTime":"09:20","endTime":"09:21","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"If we need them to send that.","startTime":"09:21","endTime":"09:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"09:25","endTime":"09:25","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or if you want to send us what is standard.","startTime":"09:25","endTime":"09:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We can see if it works or if we need to change anything.","startTime":"09:27","endTime":"09:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yep, we can do that.","startTime":"09:34","endTime":"09:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"09:35","endTime":"09:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Let me just make.","startTime":"09:38","endTime":"09:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So an action item for us is to take a screenshot of our labor quote request form and send that off to them so they can compare it against their form.","startTime":"09:39","endTime":"09:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'll trade forms and we'll collaborate and make sure we have a plan for.","startTime":"09:47","endTime":"09:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Configuration on those forms.","startTime":"09:52","endTime":"09:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"09:57","endTime":"09:57","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Some of this I can skip.","startTime":"09:59","endTime":"10:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Oh, the process of.","startTime":"10:06","endTime":"10:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, let's go back to the calculation of labor.","startTime":"10:08","endTime":"10:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you probably send it out for a bid or you get your vendor's quote back and then you're doing some kind of markup at some point on that, right?","startTime":"10:11","endTime":"10:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"10:21","endTime":"10:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"10:23","endTime":"10:23","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, the markup happens on the line and the order.","startTime":"10:23","endTime":"10:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Any expectation of any of that being in Orion or you guys just doing that in Excel right now, those calculations.","startTime":"10:28","endTime":"10:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"No, it's done in neither Project Spec.","startTime":"10:36","endTime":"10:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"What is it called?","startTime":"10:39","endTime":"10:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Kimmy?","startTime":"10:40","endTime":"10:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's in Project Spec.","startTime":"10:42","endTime":"10:43","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"But the.","startTime":"10:43","endTime":"10:44","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I was going to say, can we do the 15?","startTime":"10:45","endTime":"10:47","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, we'll get to it.","startTime":"10:48","endTime":"10:49","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Or does that.","startTime":"10:49","endTime":"10:50","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"10:50","endTime":"10:51","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah, the.","startTime":"10:51","endTime":"10:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I guess.","startTime":"10:53","endTime":"10:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I guess it depends.","startTime":"10:55","endTime":"10:56","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If we're doing a rom, it's in Excel.","startTime":"10:56","endTime":"10:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If we're Doing a proposal.","startTime":"10:58","endTime":"11:00","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"It's in core, and it either comes in on the SIF or we do it on the line in core.","startTime":"11:00","endTime":"11:04","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"11:06","endTime":"11:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"11:08","endTime":"11:08","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that would work the same way.","startTime":"11:08","endTime":"11:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Then when you're doing it inside of core, there's no.","startTime":"11:09","endTime":"11:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There's.","startTime":"11:14","endTime":"11:14","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I just want to make sure there's, like, no business logic or automated thing that's happening that's doing some kind of automated markup.","startTime":"11:14","endTime":"11:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Not automated markup.","startTime":"11:21","endTime":"11:22","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"There is doing automated deduct that Kimmy was just mentioning.","startTime":"11:22","endTime":"11:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So we have a line that is default on all orders that have labor.","startTime":"11:25","endTime":"11:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That takes a 15% off of the labor markup.","startTime":"11:30","endTime":"11:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That is basically internal cost.","startTime":"11:33","endTime":"11:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So the formula line.","startTime":"11:39","endTime":"11:40","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm hearing that correct.","startTime":"11:41","endTime":"11:42","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That's.","startTime":"11:42","endTime":"11:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That's the term in core, I think.","startTime":"11:43","endTime":"11:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yes, 15%.","startTime":"11:45","endTime":"11:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So let me just.","startTime":"11:48","endTime":"11:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I want to make sure that we get that clear for the transcript.","startTime":"11:48","endTime":"11:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"15% off labor.","startTime":"11:51","endTime":"11:53","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Off labor salve.","startTime":"11:53","endTime":"11:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Oh, okay.","startTime":"11:58","endTime":"11:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So it's looking at.","startTime":"11:58","endTime":"11:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's looking at the labor sale and then created another line.","startTime":"11:59","endTime":"12:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Wait, isn't it off of cost?","startTime":"12:03","endTime":"12:04","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Let me look at the rule right now while we're talking.","startTime":"12:06","endTime":"12:08","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":7},{"sentence":"It's taking it from the GP.","startTime":"12:09","endTime":"12:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So whatever GP you put in, it's lowering your GP.","startTime":"12:11","endTime":"12:14","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if you don't put in enough GP, it's a negative.","startTime":"12:14","endTime":"12:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If you put in more GP.","startTime":"12:16","endTime":"12:18","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Sorry, sorry.","startTime":"12:19","endTime":"12:19","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"12:19","endTime":"12:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if you put in the 35 GP and it takes 15 off, it usually makes your labor about a 25 GP by the time it's done.","startTime":"12:20","endTime":"12:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"12:28","endTime":"12:29","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Kip, when you look up that business rule, is that.","startTime":"12:29","endTime":"12:31","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is there something there?","startTime":"12:31","endTime":"12:32","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You can just take a screenshot of that for us too.","startTime":"12:32","endTime":"12:35","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Definitely.","startTime":"12:36","endTime":"12:36","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"12:36","endTime":"12:37","speaker_name":"Kip Herdrick","speaker_id":7},{"sentence":"Yeah, let's do that.","startTime":"12:38","endTime":"12:38","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That way we don't have to ask you again because we'll get in the meeting, we'll be talking about it.","startTime":"12:38","endTime":"12:43","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We're like, what was that again?","startTime":"12:43","endTime":"12:44","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, if you have any documentation, that'll help.","startTime":"12:45","endTime":"12:47","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I do.","startTime":"12:48","endTime":"12:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"12:48","endTime":"12:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Perfect.","startTime":"12:49","endTime":"12:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Thank you.","startTime":"12:49","endTime":"12:50","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So for the sake of the transcript.","startTime":"12:51","endTime":"12:52","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Kip will be sending that to us as well.","startTime":"12:52","endTime":"12:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then do you have some type of workflow for accepting those quotes from vendors?","startTime":"12:57","endTime":"13:07","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Like official acceptance and rejection?","startTime":"13:09","endTime":"13:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is that just.","startTime":"13:12","endTime":"13:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You either get a PO or you don't get a po.","startTime":"13:13","endTime":"13:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"That's our official.","startTime":"13:15","endTime":"13:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"13:18","endTime":"13:18","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"No email communication or anything like that.","startTime":"13:20","endTime":"13:22","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, sometimes there's an email communication if the PM or the AM decides to.","startTime":"13:22","endTime":"13:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But usually, you know, we put their quote number on the line and we issue a PO against that line, and our PO references their quote number, and that's our acceptance of their quote.","startTime":"13:29","endTime":"13:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Great.","startTime":"13:41","endTime":"13:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And when you're doing the labor quote.","startTime":"13:43","endTime":"13:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"You don't have your quote in the system.","startTime":"13:47","endTime":"13:48","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Well, you're building it probably in spec, right?","startTime":"13:49","endTime":"13:51","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Depends.","startTime":"13:52","endTime":"13:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Sometimes we're building it in spec, sometimes we're building it in core.","startTime":"13:53","endTime":"13:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"13:55","endTime":"13:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"When you, so you do your, you get the labor quote back and then you either going to bring that over in the sift file or you're going to put the lines on inside of core and you'll do the same thing in Orion.","startTime":"13:57","endTime":"14:10","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So we have a process in Orion where you can accept a specific labor quote and then you can also then decide what information from that labor quote wants to come over.","startTime":"14:12","endTime":"14:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So and when we get the configuration, this will make a bit more sense because we'll kind of, we'll build it out that form.","startTime":"14:20","endTime":"14:27","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'll use what you're working as a template.","startTime":"14:27","endTime":"14:29","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But typically do you bring it over as one total line or do you itemize it?","startTime":"14:29","endTime":"14:34","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I shouldn't say typically.","startTime":"14:34","endTime":"14:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Oftentimes it's one labor line, but sometimes we itemize it depending on the scope of the work.","startTime":"14:36","endTime":"14:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So if it's multi phase or we've asked for like four trip charges, but we're only going to issue a PO for one trip charge and hold back the three.","startTime":"14:41","endTime":"14:50","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So there's a lot of different stuff.","startTime":"14:50","endTime":"14:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Kimmy can speak in more depth about kind of the ways that AMs play around with that.","startTime":"14:52","endTime":"14:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"You said it pretty well.","startTime":"15:00","endTime":"15:01","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I was to say that we anticipate erosion potential through drip charges and or sometimes hold a contingency that doesn't get released.","startTime":"15:01","endTime":"15:12","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So we will add lines that are part of a grouped labor cell line and only issue the PoS related to the quoted cost that we are accepting.","startTime":"15:12","endTime":"15:26","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"15:27","endTime":"15:28","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So we might ask them to over quote, but then we'll under issue the po hoping that we don't have to use the difference.","startTime":"15:29","endTime":"15:36","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And if we do have to use the difference, it's in there.","startTime":"15:36","endTime":"15:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"And then we'll issue the PO as it's requested.","startTime":"15:38","endTime":"15:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But.","startTime":"15:40","endTime":"15:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, but we're hoping.","startTime":"15:42","endTime":"15:45","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"To hold on to that money.","startTime":"15:45","endTime":"15:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"We GSI build a client, right.","startTime":"15:46","endTime":"15:49","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"If we do a good job, we take what we kept as our reward.","startTime":"15:49","endTime":"15:52","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So sure, yeah.","startTime":"15:52","endTime":"15:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Got it.","startTime":"15:54","endTime":"15:54","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then going back, I do like.","startTime":"15:56","endTime":"15:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The idea of being able to though.","startTime":"15:59","endTime":"16:00","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Like if a labor quote comes in, if we send out a labor quote request, it comes back in and then we can.","startTime":"16:00","endTime":"16:05","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Where we spend a lot of time is copying and pasting.","startTime":"16:06","endTime":"16:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So like the less copy and pasting we can do to get it to what it needs to be.","startTime":"16:08","endTime":"16:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"You know, there's a method that Orion has built in to do that, then we definitely want to look at what that process change could be.","startTime":"16:13","endTime":"16:22","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"16:22","endTime":"16:23","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, definitely.","startTime":"16:23","endTime":"16:24","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There's a labor quote acceptance feature and there's like a little modal that says, okay, I'm going to accept this labor quote and I'm going to decide what lines I want to have pass over to the quote, record either summary or itemized.","startTime":"16:24","endTime":"16:38","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And you can kind of.","startTime":"16:38","endTime":"16:39","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"You can kind of fiddle with that a little bit.","startTime":"16:39","endTime":"16:41","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then it connects the quote and the labor quote together and it makes labor quote part of the project.","startTime":"16:41","endTime":"16:46","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So when we're doing all our project reporting later on, you have visibility starting at the labor quote, to the quote, to the sales order, to the invoice.","startTime":"16:46","endTime":"16:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And you know exactly yet you see all those costs and even purchase orders and bills.","startTime":"16:56","endTime":"17:01","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So you can have that visibility.","startTime":"17:02","endTime":"17:04","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And I'm thinking also, since you are, it's decentralized as far as who can send this out for quote.","startTime":"17:06","endTime":"17:11","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I imagine as far as accepting it is also decentralized.","startTime":"17:11","endTime":"17:15","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"There's not any specific person that could do the acceptance.","startTime":"17:15","endTime":"17:18","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's really whoever's managing that.","startTime":"17:18","endTime":"17:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm assuming there's not like a rubber stamp by any means.","startTime":"17:20","endTime":"17:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Usually it's the account manager or the salesperson that's going to accept the final labor number or the PM if they get some help.","startTime":"17:25","endTime":"17:34","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Marcus, last month I requested like 50 labor quotes.","startTime":"17:34","endTime":"17:37","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So it's like anybody is available.","startTime":"17:37","endTime":"17:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"If you're willing and know how to, you can request a labor quote.","startTime":"17:39","endTime":"17:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Oftentimes what PMs are doing is they're presenting what they think we should do.","startTime":"17:43","endTime":"17:48","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"So they might go get three quotes and then they make a recommendation.","startTime":"17:48","endTime":"17:51","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"But ultimately it's the sales side that makes the final decision on what labor we're going to use.","startTime":"17:52","endTime":"17:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"17:58","endTime":"17:58","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"17:58","endTime":"17:59","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So this is a little bit different than some of the other dealers we work with.","startTime":"18:00","endTime":"18:02","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"With other dealers.","startTime":"18:02","endTime":"18:03","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's a bit more centralized with some other dealers.","startTime":"18:03","endTime":"18:06","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That's why I'm asking some of these clarifying questions.","startTime":"18:07","endTime":"18:09","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I just want to make sure that our team has a clear understanding on how you guys are working.","startTime":"18:09","endTime":"18:13","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And I could see the benefit of multiple people being able to do this because it's not bottlenecked through one person or two people.","startTime":"18:13","endTime":"18:20","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, well, we have so many different markets and market requirements.","startTime":"18:21","endTime":"18:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Kimmy, you have a thought?","startTime":"18:25","endTime":"18:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"What are you thinking?","startTime":"18:27","endTime":"18:28","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Well, I was.","startTime":"18:28","endTime":"18:29","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I was going to ask a clarification question about something Marcus said that I didn't fully understand about.","startTime":"18:30","endTime":"18:36","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"You mentioned something about the labor quote and tying it to the order.","startTime":"18:37","endTime":"18:42","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Like, wouldn't.","startTime":"18:43","endTime":"18:44","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It does it like live freely without association to quote until you tie it.","startTime":"18:44","endTime":"18:50","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"I guess I just don't understand that portion of it.","startTime":"18:50","endTime":"18:54","speaker_name":"Kimi Katsuyoshi","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"18:54","endTime":"18:55","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So the idea here is.","startTime":"18:55","endTime":"18:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"18:56","endTime":"18:56","speaker_name":"Marcus Dallacqua","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The labor quote is this standalone record, and you could have multiple labor quotes because you may have sent multiple out, got multiple back, and now you got to choose which one.","startTime":"18:56","endTime":"19:07","speaker_nam