ble, it can be on a dashboard, it can be automatically emailed to one or more people on a schedule.","startTime":"18:59","endTime":"19:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"There's all kinds of stuff we can do with that.","startTime":"19:06","endTime":"19:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And we can have a client version and an internal version.","startTime":"19:09","endTime":"19:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"19:12","endTime":"19:14","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"You just run different data.","startTime":"19:14","endTime":"19:17","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I, I don't know if what segment we talk about that, if it's just a report and maybe it's.","startTime":"19:19","endTime":"19:24","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I'm over complicating it but that's a major touch point currently for AMS and PCs I'm really curious about.","startTime":"19:24","endTime":"19:34","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yeah, just nail networks and works.","startTime":"19:34","endTime":"19:36","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, yeah.","startTime":"19:37","endTime":"19:38","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"We do get into some reports in business intelligence, but it's those little things like that sometimes you gloss over.","startTime":"19:38","endTime":"19:44","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"You know, you say like these are.","startTime":"19:44","endTime":"19:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"All our important reports and then it's important to like highlight that one.","startTime":"19:45","endTime":"19:49","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"One of that type to make sure we get it nailed down and specified.","startTime":"19:49","endTime":"19:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, yeah, make a note of that.","startTime":"19:55","endTime":"19:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then it's asking.","startTime":"20:00","endTime":"20:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, so I have some questions from the questionnaire that I think I know the answer to, but, like.","startTime":"20:02","endTime":"20:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like, obviously they should only be able to see their own deals and work orders.","startTime":"20:10","endTime":"20:13","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Is there any limit or is there any scope of, like, project information that people would need to see or pricing information?","startTime":"20:13","endTime":"20:20","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"No, we don't show any of our.","startTime":"20:23","endTime":"20:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Well, I mean, I guess.","startTime":"20:25","endTime":"20:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Are we talking about labor vendors?","startTime":"20:25","endTime":"20:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Are we talking about all vendors?","startTime":"20:27","endTime":"20:28","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So this.","startTime":"20:29","endTime":"20:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I think this would specifically be for labor vendors.","startTime":"20:30","endTime":"20:33","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like, obviously, other vendors are going to see their transaction.","startTime":"20:33","endTime":"20:35","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, they only just see their pos.","startTime":"20:36","endTime":"20:37","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We don't share any of our product pricing with them.","startTime":"20:38","endTime":"20:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Perfect, perfect.","startTime":"20:41","endTime":"20:42","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"20:42","endTime":"20:43","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And then what's the process for sharing documentation with, like, a labor vendor?","startTime":"20:43","endTime":"20:50","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"We share documents, their drive.","startTime":"20:50","endTime":"20:52","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"20:52","endTime":"20:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And it's just links out to your drive currently.","startTime":"20:53","endTime":"20:55","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"20:56","endTime":"20:56","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"20:57","endTime":"20:58","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Receiving tickets, right?","startTime":"21:00","endTime":"21:02","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Like, where we give the labor company what they are expected to receive.","startTime":"21:02","endTime":"21:06","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yes.","startTime":"21:06","endTime":"21:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"We can do receiving tickets.","startTime":"21:07","endTime":"21:08","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"21:08","endTime":"21:09","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Can we automate it so they just get sent when we place an order?","startTime":"21:11","endTime":"21:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"21:16","endTime":"21:16","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Oh, my gosh, that'd be wonderful.","startTime":"21:16","endTime":"21:18","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"Yeah, that's.","startTime":"21:18","endTime":"21:19","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's like, just at a high level.","startTime":"21:20","endTime":"21:22","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Just think, like, if the data's in.","startTime":"21:22","endTime":"21:23","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The system, it will go somewhere.","startTime":"21:23","endTime":"21:25","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If you wanted to.","startTime":"21:25","endTime":"21:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If you wanted to go somewhere.","startTime":"21:26","endTime":"21:27","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"We go wherever you want.","startTime":"21:27","endTime":"21:28","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"21:28","endTime":"21:29","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"21:29","endTime":"21:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"21:30","endTime":"21:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"You just have to decide the method of notification.","startTime":"21:30","endTime":"21:32","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like, is it an email?","startTime":"21:32","endTime":"21:34","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Does the email go out every time something is added to that list, or do you want it to go out on a schedule?","startTime":"21:34","endTime":"21:39","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Things like that.","startTime":"21:39","endTime":"21:39","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"21:40","endTime":"21:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"21:41","endTime":"21:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"21:42","endTime":"21:43","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So let's talk a little bit about the VRA process.","startTime":"21:43","endTime":"21:47","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Things like damage on the vendor return authorization process.","startTime":"21:49","endTime":"21:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, so things like damage on arrival, vendor.","startTime":"21:56","endTime":"22:00","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"This is coming from your product vendors.","startTime":"22:00","endTime":"22:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you use a vendor return process at all today?","startTime":"22:04","endTime":"22:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or how do you interchange with a vendor for issues that come up with product?","startTime":"22:07","endTime":"22:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So you mean things that are going to go back to the warehouse?","startTime":"22:13","endTime":"22:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, back to the vendor.","startTime":"22:17","endTime":"22:19","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like a manufacturer's warehouse, for example.","startTime":"22:19","endTime":"22:21","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Oh, like back to a manufacturer.","startTime":"22:21","endTime":"22:23","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, we don't typically ever.","startTime":"22:23","endTime":"22:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's very rare that we represent anything back to a manufacturer.","startTime":"22:27","endTime":"22:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, that's good.","startTime":"22:30","endTime":"22:31","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:31","endTime":"22:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:32","endTime":"22:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So right now, we did.","startTime":"22:33","endTime":"22:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Usually what happens is they send us a bill of lading and we tell them where to pick it up from.","startTime":"22:35","endTime":"22:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"22:43","endTime":"22:43","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:44","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:44","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So that's like the.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:45","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The kind of ad hoc process if it does happen, but there isn't a solid process, like, it doesn't happen enough to have a solid process of, like, this Is exactly how we handle it.","startTime":"22:45","endTime":"22:54","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"No, no.","startTime":"22:55","endTime":"22:56","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I don't think so.","startTime":"22:56","endTime":"22:56","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"How nice is that?","startTime":"22:57","endTime":"22:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, right.","startTime":"22:58","endTime":"22:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So then don't jinx us.","startTime":"23:00","endTime":"23:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, I would love if they would take stuff back when we order it wrong, but they'll.","startTime":"23:02","endTime":"23:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"They never seem to want to send a truck for that.","startTime":"23:06","endTime":"23:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so then that kind of brings up.","startTime":"23:08","endTime":"23:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So then what do you.","startTime":"23:11","endTime":"23:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you have, like, damaged products sitting in bins somewhere?","startTime":"23:12","endTime":"23:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The reality of it is if they either.","startTime":"23:17","endTime":"23:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"They'll send us parts if it's fixable, and if it's not fixable, then it gets disposed of and they send a whole new product.","startTime":"23:20","endTime":"23:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so it never really sits there at all.","startTime":"23:29","endTime":"23:33","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Not usually.","startTime":"23:34","endTime":"23:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, there have been a few times where, like, they've flown people out from the factory to fix stuff in the field.","startTime":"23:35","endTime":"23:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I think there might have been, like, one or two times where they wanted to pick it up and take it back to the factory to fix it and send it back out.","startTime":"23:41","endTime":"23:49","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But again, all we do is tell them where it is, and they work on figuring out how to go get it and get it back and then send it back to us.","startTime":"23:49","endTime":"23:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"23:57","endTime":"23:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"23:57","endTime":"23:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's really more of a manufacturer process than our process.","startTime":"23:58","endTime":"24:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process is just to notify them that there's an issue and wait for them to tell us how they want to solve it.","startTime":"24:01","endTime":"24:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so then these next few questions might apply or not apply.","startTime":"24:06","endTime":"24:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Chris, can I ask just before you do that?","startTime":"24:11","endTime":"24:13","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So if it.","startTime":"24:14","endTime":"24:15","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So your question about, you know, does it go into a bin for damaged.","startTime":"24:17","endTime":"24:21","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It sounds like.","startTime":"24:21","endTime":"24:22","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Matt, you tell them to go pick it up at a customer site.","startTime":"24:23","endTime":"24:27","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's not at your location?","startTime":"24:27","endTime":"24:29","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Well, I mean, because Debbie says we don't have a location.","startTime":"24:30","endTime":"24:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It might be at the warehouse, but it's not our warehouse.","startTime":"24:33","endTime":"24:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So we don't have any bin set up for in our system.","startTime":"24:35","endTime":"24:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It just gets marked as punch.","startTime":"24:38","endTime":"24:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So in core, that means a little flame shows up next to the line, and, you know, the flame stays there until it's resolved.","startTime":"24:40","endTime":"24:47","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But we.","startTime":"24:48","endTime":"24:48","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process for that, I guess.","startTime":"24:49","endTime":"24:50","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process isn't focused about the return our processes.","startTime":"24:52","endTime":"24:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That would be a punch process.","startTime":"24:55","endTime":"24:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"24:58","endTime":"24:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So literally, order management, we would go to that line.","startTime":"24:59","endTime":"25:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'd mark that line as a punch issue, and then we would detail what the punch issue is, and it would stay a punch issue till it's resolved.","startTime":"25:02","endTime":"25:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"One of the options to resolve it might be the manufacturer wants to pick up that product and repair it and send it back out.","startTime":"25:10","endTime":"25:17","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"25:17","endTime":"25:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"25:18","endTime":"25:18","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Thank you for that.","startTime":"25:18","endTime":"25:19","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"25:19","endTime":"25:20","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Sorry.","startTime":"25:20","endTime":"25:20","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"In terms of, like, the financial impact of that Is there any, like, do you write it off?","startTime":"25:21","endTime":"25:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you?","startTime":"25:28","endTime":"25:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It depends.","startTime":"25:29","endTime":"25:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if it's a war of.","startTime":"25:30","endTime":"25:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If we're disposing of because we damaged it, then the warehouse might send us the cost to dispose.","startTime":"25:32","endTime":"25:39","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And so then we would add a line for service on the order for that cost.","startTime":"25:41","endTime":"25:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Or if the client has asked us to dispose of something, then we would add a line and then we would put a cell on it.","startTime":"25:47","endTime":"25:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It wouldn't be a cost only event.","startTime":"25:53","endTime":"25:54","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that's all really taken care of still at the order management level.","startTime":"25:55","endTime":"25:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Gotcha.","startTime":"25:59","endTime":"25:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then does that affect a specific GL account?","startTime":"25:59","endTime":"26:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Is this part of cost of goods sold or.","startTime":"26:04","endTime":"26:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Cost of goods sold.","startTime":"26:06","endTime":"26:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Good.","startTime":"26:07","endTime":"26:08","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"26:10","endTime":"26:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Lorraine, did I speak correctly?","startTime":"26:10","endTime":"26:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That.","startTime":"26:11","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"26:12","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"26:12","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then this seems really granular, but one of the questions is what if a vendor comes.","startTime":"26:13","endTime":"26:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"If a vendor credit comes in during a different accounting period than the damage occurred, does that happen or is there any concern for that?","startTime":"26:18","endTime":"26:26","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I mean, it just goes towards that project.","startTime":"26:27","endTime":"26:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So, like, if we build back the way we build back a vendor now, if, like, if they're at fault for something or they create damage or they create a delay and they're going to pay us for that, we send them a proposal as a customer.","startTime":"26:30","endTime":"26:43","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So most of our vendors are also set up as a customer.","startTime":"26:43","endTime":"26:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"26:45","endTime":"26:46","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And we'll send them a proposal.","startTime":"26:46","endTime":"26:48","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'll put the sell on that proposal, and then.","startTime":"26:48","endTime":"26:51","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Basically we'll do a credit line credit.","startTime":"26:55","endTime":"26:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm trying to remember the right terminology, Kimmy, you might have to help me out with this if you remember.","startTime":"26:58","endTime":"27:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But basically, like, we bill it on this proposal and then we apply a credit to the proposal that was affected by whatever, wherever that cost happened.","startTime":"27:01","endTime":"27:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The original one.","startTime":"27:11","endTime":"27:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"27:12","endTime":"27:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"27:12","endTime":"27:13","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So I don't think that we.","startTime":"27:13","endTime":"27:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, Lorraine, we've never tracked it any other way.","startTime":"27:15","endTime":"27:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is there any reason why that would be a problem continuing?","startTime":"27:19","endTime":"27:22","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If it happens in different months or different quarters, it just kind of hits when it hits.","startTime":"27:22","endTime":"27:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"27:27","endTime":"27:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"A credit from a vendor.","startTime":"27:27","endTime":"27:28","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"