ly in this scenario I would advocate that they would also just generate a blank work order with the future install date to then be modified when more information and a PM is available to then actually modify in detail that.","startTime":"44:19","endTime":"44:35","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Specific work order and solidify the actual date.","startTime":"44:35","endTime":"44:39","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It's going to happen.","startTime":"44:39","endTime":"44:40","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Right?","startTime":"44:40","endTime":"44:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"44:41","endTime":"44:42","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So there's like fictitious until like the product is actually acknowledged and received at the warehouse.","startTime":"44:42","endTime":"44:49","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Exactly, yeah.","startTime":"44:50","endTime":"44:51","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So there are two stages of that.","startTime":"44:51","endTime":"44:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like there is creating the work order and the work order events.","startTime":"44:53","endTime":"44:56","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And when you're creating a work order event, you're selecting a date, but then it kind of goes into an approval queue.","startTime":"44:56","endTime":"45:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And so people are looking at a date and saying, okay, these are all the things that got requested for this date.","startTime":"45:02","endTime":"45:08","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then you're actually dragging them over like, yes, it's approved on that date.","startTime":"45:08","endTime":"45:11","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Here's all the resources I need.","startTime":"45:11","endTime":"45:13","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"That's like part of the scheduling and dispatch.","startTime":"45:14","endTime":"45:16","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Which is separate than this because that's a bigger, more holistic conversation regarding multiple jobs in review.","startTime":"45:18","endTime":"45:25","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"45:26","endTime":"45:26","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"45:26","endTime":"45:27","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Well, for me, like my thought is if you flip an order, every project needs a site verification.","startTime":"45:27","endTime":"45:34","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Every project needs, you know, a punch walk.","startTime":"45:34","endTime":"45:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So it's like they're all sitting there ready to go, waiting to happen.","startTime":"45:38","endTime":"45:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And you then go in and modify them to put in who is going to do them and when they're going to do them.","startTime":"45:41","endTime":"45:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But it's almost like a list of tasks that have to happen on every project.","startTime":"45:47","endTime":"45:51","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, so.","startTime":"45:54","endTime":"45:55","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Right, yeah, it is a list of tasks.","startTime":"45:56","endTime":"45:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"If you do it as a work order event, it obviously opens up a lot more information.","startTime":"46:00","endTime":"46:06","speaker_name":"Chris Tr