endTime":"21:41","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"21:41","endTime":"21:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"21:42","endTime":"21:43","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So let's talk a little bit about the VRA process.","startTime":"21:43","endTime":"21:47","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Things like damage on the vendor return authorization process.","startTime":"21:49","endTime":"21:53","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Okay, so things like damage on arrival, vendor.","startTime":"21:56","endTime":"22:00","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"This is coming from your product vendors.","startTime":"22:00","endTime":"22:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you use a vendor return process at all today?","startTime":"22:04","endTime":"22:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or how do you interchange with a vendor for issues that come up with product?","startTime":"22:07","endTime":"22:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So you mean things that are going to go back to the warehouse?","startTime":"22:13","endTime":"22:16","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, back to the vendor.","startTime":"22:17","endTime":"22:19","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like a manufacturer's warehouse, for example.","startTime":"22:19","endTime":"22:21","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Oh, like back to a manufacturer.","startTime":"22:21","endTime":"22:23","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, we don't typically ever.","startTime":"22:23","endTime":"22:26","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's very rare that we represent anything back to a manufacturer.","startTime":"22:27","endTime":"22:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, that's good.","startTime":"22:30","endTime":"22:31","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:31","endTime":"22:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:32","endTime":"22:32","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So right now, we did.","startTime":"22:33","endTime":"22:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Usually what happens is they send us a bill of lading and we tell them where to pick it up from.","startTime":"22:35","endTime":"22:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"22:43","endTime":"22:43","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:44","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:44","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So that's like the.","startTime":"22:44","endTime":"22:45","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The kind of ad hoc process if it does happen, but there isn't a solid process, like, it doesn't happen enough to have a solid process of, like, this Is exactly how we handle it.","startTime":"22:45","endTime":"22:54","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"No, no.","startTime":"22:55","endTime":"22:56","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I don't think so.","startTime":"22:56","endTime":"22:56","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"How nice is that?","startTime":"22:57","endTime":"22:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah, right.","startTime":"22:58","endTime":"22:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So then don't jinx us.","startTime":"23:00","endTime":"23:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, I would love if they would take stuff back when we order it wrong, but they'll.","startTime":"23:02","endTime":"23:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"They never seem to want to send a truck for that.","startTime":"23:06","endTime":"23:08","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so then that kind of brings up.","startTime":"23:08","endTime":"23:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So then what do you.","startTime":"23:11","endTime":"23:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you have, like, damaged products sitting in bins somewhere?","startTime":"23:12","endTime":"23:15","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"The reality of it is if they either.","startTime":"23:17","endTime":"23:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"They'll send us parts if it's fixable, and if it's not fixable, then it gets disposed of and they send a whole new product.","startTime":"23:20","endTime":"23:29","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so it never really sits there at all.","startTime":"23:29","endTime":"23:33","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Not usually.","startTime":"23:34","endTime":"23:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, there have been a few times where, like, they've flown people out from the factory to fix stuff in the field.","startTime":"23:35","endTime":"23:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I think there might have been, like, one or two times where they wanted to pick it up and take it back to the factory to fix it and send it back out.","startTime":"23:41","endTime":"23:49","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But again, all we do is tell them where it is, and they work on figuring out how to go get it and get it back and then send it back to us.","startTime":"23:49","endTime":"23:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So.","startTime":"23:57","endTime":"23:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"23:57","endTime":"23:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It's really more of a manufacturer process than our process.","startTime":"23:58","endTime":"24:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process is just to notify them that there's an issue and wait for them to tell us how they want to solve it.","startTime":"24:01","endTime":"24:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay, so then these next few questions might apply or not apply.","startTime":"24:06","endTime":"24:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Chris, can I ask just before you do that?","startTime":"24:11","endTime":"24:13","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So if it.","startTime":"24:14","endTime":"24:15","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"So your question about, you know, does it go into a bin for damaged.","startTime":"24:17","endTime":"24:21","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It sounds like.","startTime":"24:21","endTime":"24:22","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Matt, you tell them to go pick it up at a customer site.","startTime":"24:23","endTime":"24:27","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"It's not at your location?","startTime":"24:27","endTime":"24:29","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Well, I mean, because Debbie says we don't have a location.","startTime":"24:30","endTime":"24:33","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It might be at the warehouse, but it's not our warehouse.","startTime":"24:33","endTime":"24:35","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So we don't have any bin set up for in our system.","startTime":"24:35","endTime":"24:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It just gets marked as punch.","startTime":"24:38","endTime":"24:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So in core, that means a little flame shows up next to the line, and, you know, the flame stays there until it's resolved.","startTime":"24:40","endTime":"24:47","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But we.","startTime":"24:48","endTime":"24:48","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process for that, I guess.","startTime":"24:49","endTime":"24:50","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Our process isn't focused about the return our processes.","startTime":"24:52","endTime":"24:55","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That would be a punch process.","startTime":"24:55","endTime":"24:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"24:58","endTime":"24:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So literally, order management, we would go to that line.","startTime":"24:59","endTime":"25:02","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'd mark that line as a punch issue, and then we would detail what the punch issue is, and it would stay a punch issue till it's resolved.","startTime":"25:02","endTime":"25:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"One of the options to resolve it might be the manufacturer wants to pick up that product and repair it and send it back out.","startTime":"25:10","endTime":"25:17","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"25:17","endTime":"25:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"25:18","endTime":"25:18","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Thank you for that.","startTime":"25:18","endTime":"25:19","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"25:19","endTime":"25:20","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Sorry.","startTime":"25:20","endTime":"25:20","speaker_name":"Debbie Herbert","speaker_id":3},{"sentence":"In terms of, like, the financial impact of that Is there any, like, do you write it off?","startTime":"25:21","endTime":"25:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Do you?","startTime":"25:28","endTime":"25:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It depends.","startTime":"25:29","endTime":"25:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So if it's a war of.","startTime":"25:30","endTime":"25:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If we're disposing of because we damaged it, then the warehouse might send us the cost to dispose.","startTime":"25:32","endTime":"25:39","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And so then we would add a line for service on the order for that cost.","startTime":"25:41","endTime":"25:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Or if the client has asked us to dispose of something, then we would add a line and then we would put a cell on it.","startTime":"25:47","endTime":"25:53","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"It wouldn't be a cost only event.","startTime":"25:53","endTime":"25:54","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So that's all really taken care of still at the order management level.","startTime":"25:55","endTime":"25:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Gotcha.","startTime":"25:59","endTime":"25:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then does that affect a specific GL account?","startTime":"25:59","endTime":"26:02","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Is this part of cost of goods sold or.","startTime":"26:04","endTime":"26:06","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Cost of goods sold.","startTime":"26:06","endTime":"26:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Good.","startTime":"26:07","endTime":"26:08","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"26:10","endTime":"26:10","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Lorraine, did I speak correctly?","startTime":"26:10","endTime":"26:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"That.","startTime":"26:11","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"26:12","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"26:12","endTime":"26:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then this seems really granular, but one of the questions is what if a vendor comes.","startTime":"26:13","endTime":"26:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"If a vendor credit comes in during a different accounting period than the damage occurred, does that happen or is there any concern for that?","startTime":"26:18","endTime":"26:26","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I mean, it just goes towards that project.","startTime":"26:27","endTime":"26:30","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So, like, if we build back the way we build back a vendor now, if, like, if they're at fault for something or they create damage or they create a delay and they're going to pay us for that, we send them a proposal as a customer.","startTime":"26:30","endTime":"26:43","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So most of our vendors are also set up as a customer.","startTime":"26:43","endTime":"26:45","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"26:45","endTime":"26:46","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And we'll send them a proposal.","startTime":"26:46","endTime":"26:48","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We'll put the sell on that proposal, and then.","startTime":"26:48","endTime":"26:51","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Basically we'll do a credit line credit.","startTime":"26:55","endTime":"26:58","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I'm trying to remember the right terminology, Kimmy, you might have to help me out with this if you remember.","startTime":"26:58","endTime":"27:01","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But basically, like, we bill it on this proposal and then we apply a credit to the proposal that was affected by whatever, wherever that cost happened.","startTime":"27:01","endTime":"27:11","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"The original one.","startTime":"27:11","endTime":"27:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"27:12","endTime":"27:12","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"27:12","endTime":"27:13","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So I don't think that we.","startTime":"27:13","endTime":"27:15","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I mean, Lorraine, we've never tracked it any other way.","startTime":"27:15","endTime":"27:19","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Is there any reason why that would be a problem continuing?","startTime":"27:19","endTime":"27:22","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"If it happens in different months or different quarters, it just kind of hits when it hits.","startTime":"27:22","endTime":"27:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"27:27","endTime":"27:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"A credit from a vendor.","startTime":"27:27","endTime":"27:28","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"27:29","endTime":"27:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"27:30","endTime":"27:30","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And then if you.","startTime":"27:31","endTime":"27:33","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"I don't.","startTime":"27:33","endTime":"27:33","speaker_name":"Wendy Stark","speaker_id":5},{"sentence":"I don't do any accruals or booking of any of that.","startTime":"27:33","endTime":"27:36","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":7},{"sentence":"It happens in real time.","startTime":"27:36","endTime":"27:37","speaker_name":"Lorraine Guzman","speaker_id":7},{"sentence":"I guess the way we do it, Chris, the reason it doesn't matter is we put the cost on the original order and then we sell it and we wait for that sell to come in and we don't apply that credit to that cost until the cell comes in.","startTime":"27:38","endTime":"27:50","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So it sits on our books as a liability until the revenue comes in and then we credit it so that it's off the books.","startTime":"27:50","endTime":"27:57","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"27:57","endTime":"27:58","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Yeah, that Makes sense.","startTime":"27:58","endTime":"27:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Or in the case where you have zero costs, like kind of a replacement line or zero cost.","startTime":"28:01","endTime":"28:07","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Line, how does that affect the project gp?","startTime":"28:08","endTime":"28:12","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"A zero cost or a zero sell A zero.","startTime":"28:14","endTime":"28:17","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"I guess both sides of it.","startTime":"28:18","endTime":"28:20","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"We're probably good.","startTime":"28:20","endTime":"28:21","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"We put in a cell only line that inflates the gp.","startTime":"28:21","endTime":"28:24","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"28:25","endTime":"28:25","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"And if we put in a cost.","startTime":"28:26","endTime":"28:27","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Why would you do that?","startTime":"28:28","endTime":"28:29","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"For a damage.","startTime":"28:29","endTime":"28:29","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Like it would just be zero on both sides.","startTime":"28:30","endTime":"28:32","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"28:32","endTime":"28:33","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"For a damage.","startTime":"28:33","endTime":"28:34","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I mean if they're giving us a free replacement, then we would just put in a zero cost, zero cell line.","startTime":"28:34","endTime":"28:39","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"28:40","endTime":"28:40","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"28:42","endTime":"28:42","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Okay.","startTime":"28:42","endTime":"28:42","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"All right.","startTime":"28:44","endTime":"28:44","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So there's no impact to project profitability if that's the case.","startTime":"28:44","endTime":"28:48","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"And then it's like assuming because there is a VRA process.","startTime":"28:51","endTime":"28:57","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"It doesn't sound like that we need to set up any kind of complicated workflow.","startTime":"28:57","endTime":"29:00","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Like, you know, there's like, you know, you can get deep like people have deep vendor return processes where there's permissions required and all that stuff.","startTime":"29:00","endTime":"29:10","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"But we don't really need that process because it's all handled pretty, you know.","startTime":"29:10","endTime":"29:14","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Pretty smoothly without it.","startTime":"29:16","endTime":"29:18","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"I mean, I don't know if I'm just basic, but it feels like overkill.","startTime":"29:18","endTime":"29:23","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"We don't want to be in the business of returning stuff.","startTime":"29:24","endTime":"29:27","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"I know.","startTime":"29:27","endTime":"29:28","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Yeah.","startTime":"29:28","endTime":"29:29","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Well, and we also aren't in the business of over building processes.","startTime":"29:29","endTime":"29:31","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"29:33","endTime":"29:33","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"So there was earlier discussion about an for credit management and end of the month credit report.","startTime":"29:36","endTime":"29:42","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Marcus had discussed it in a previous session.","startTime":"29:42","endTime":"29:44","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"So maybe.","star