r_id":1},{"sentence":"Here's all the resources I need.","startTime":"45:11","endTime":"45:13","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"That's like part of the scheduling and dispatch.","startTime":"45:14","endTime":"45:16","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Which is separate than this because that's a bigger, more holistic conversation regarding multiple jobs in review.","startTime":"45:18","endTime":"45:25","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Yep.","startTime":"45:26","endTime":"45:26","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"Right.","startTime":"45:26","endTime":"45:27","speaker_name":"+14*******45","speaker_id":6},{"sentence":"Well, for me, like my thought is if you flip an order, every project needs a site verification.","startTime":"45:27","endTime":"45:34","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Every project needs, you know, a punch walk.","startTime":"45:34","endTime":"45:38","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"So it's like they're all sitting there ready to go, waiting to happen.","startTime":"45:38","endTime":"45:41","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"And you then go in and modify them to put in who is going to do them and when they're going to do them.","startTime":"45:41","endTime":"45:46","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"But it's almost like a list of tasks that have to happen on every project.","startTime":"45:47","endTime":"45:51","speaker_name":"Matt Denning","speaker_id":2},{"sentence":"Yeah, so.","startTime":"45:54","endTime":"45:55","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":1},{"sentence":"Right, yeah, it is a list of tasks.","startTime":"45:56","endTime":"45:59","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble","speaker_id":0},{"sentence":"If you do it as a work order event, it obviously opens up a lot more information.","startTime":"46:00","endTime":"46:06","speaker_name":"Chris Trumble"