./_Unification/working/codex-run.log:894:    27	KBM's 5-year prepayment is a financial asset that does not transfer if the account is abandoned. Walking away from it to consolidate inside Pivot's account would mean writing off the prepaid value and continuing to pay annual fees indefinitely — the worst possible combination. Continuing inside KBM and letting Pivot's contract lapse at renewal preserves the asset and removes a recurring cost.
./_Unification/working/codex-run.log:896:    29	NetSuite leadership confirmed this same posture in our recent meeting: their preferred path is for the merged company to operate inside the prepaid KBM account. NetSuite will not consolidate the two accounts (they would lose revenue), but they are not opposed to one of them lapsing — and Pivot's annual structure makes the lapse mechanically simple.
./_Unification/working/codex-run.log:900:    33	1. **Do not renew the Pivot Interiors NetSuite contract.** Allow it to lapse at the May 2026 renewal date. No counter-offer, no extension.
